<subSubSection id="87B46525FFE9FFF3FF6950C1FB7728EF" pageId="22" pageNumber="188" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFE9FFF3FF6950C1FECE299C" blockId="22.[189,310,653,679]" box="[189,310,653,679]" pageId="22" pageNumber="188">
<heading id="945981C2FFE9FFF3FF6950C1FECE299C" bold="true" box="[189,310,653,679]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="22" pageNumber="188" reason="3">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFE9FFF3FF6950C1FECE299C" bold="true" box="[189,310,653,679]" pageId="22" pageNumber="188">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFE9FFF3FF6950F0FB7728EF" blockId="22.[188,1399,700,980]" pageId="22" pageNumber="188">
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFE9FFF3FEE750F1FE4B29ED" authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2022" box="[307,435,701,726]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraiso" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFE9FFF3FEE750F1FE4B29ED" box="[307,435,701,726]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="188">N. paraiso</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E6E957C7FFE9FFF3FE6F50F1FDE129EC" box="[443,537,701,727]" pageId="22" pageNumber="188" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFE9FFF3FCD050F1FC7829ED" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayon" authorityYear="2016" box="[772,896,700,726]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elverde">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFE9FFF3FCD050F1FC7829ED" box="[772,896,700,726]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="188">N. elverde</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AB3F4B5FFFE9FFF3FC4650F0FB4A29ED" author="Rheims C. A. &amp; Alayon G." box="[914,1202,700,727]" pageId="22" pageNumber="188" pagination="301 - 344" refId="ref12419" refString="Rheims C. A. &amp; Alayon G. 2016. Neostasina gen. nov., a new genus of huntsman spiders from the Neotropical region (Araneae, Sparassidae, Sparianthinae). Zootaxa 4079: 301 - 344. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4079.3.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Rheims &amp; Alayón 2016</bibRefCitation>
: figs 53−56) by the vRTA and dRTA of similar size, E filiform, TBE bifid and subdistally bent retrolaterally and TBC slightly longer than MA. They are distinguished from the latter species by the vRTA pointed and TBE with secondary branch arising medially (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFE9FFF3FD415165FD132878" box="[661,747,809,835]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[189,232,1752,1778]" captionTargetBox="[198,1398,371,1626]" captionTargetId="figure-15@25.[189,1399,361,1664]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 14. Neostasina paraiso sp. nov., A−D: holotype, ♂ (USNM), E−G: paratype, ♀ (USNM). A. Left palp, prolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. TBE, detail, ventral view. E. Epigyne, dorsal view. F. Vulva, ventral view. G. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ag = anterior groove; ar = anterior rim; C = conductor; CD = copulatory duct; dRTA = dorsal branch of RTA; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; LL = lateral lobe; MA = median apophysis; MS = median septum; pt = tegular protrusion; RpPt = cymbial retroproximal protrusion; SP = spermathecae; TBC = tegular projection at base of conductor; TBE = tegular projection at base of embolus; vRTA = ventral branch of RTA; VTA = ventral tibial apophysis. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607950" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607950/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="188">Figs 14</figureCitation>
B−D) (vRTA distally blunt; TBE with secondary branch arising subdistally, close to tip in 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFE9FFF3FD8A5102FD21285C" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayon" authorityYear="2016" box="[606,729,845,871]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elverde">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFE9FFF3FD8A5102FD21285C" box="[606,729,845,871]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="188">N. elverde</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Females resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFE9FFF3FB905102FB10285C" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayon" authorityYear="2016" box="[1092,1256,846,871]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jamaicana">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFE9FFF3FB905102FB10285C" box="[1092,1256,846,871]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="188">N. jamaicana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AB3F4B5FFFE9FFF3FB2E5101FEA128B0" author="Rheims C. A. &amp; Alayon G." pageId="22" pageNumber="188" pagination="301 - 344" refId="ref12419" refString="Rheims C. A. &amp; Alayon G. 2016. Neostasina gen. nov., a new genus of huntsman spiders from the Neotropical region (Araneae, Sparassidae, Sparianthinae). Zootaxa 4079: 301 - 344. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4079.3.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Rheims &amp; Alayón 2016</bibRefCitation>
: figs 79−81) by the epigyne with EF bearing an anterior groove. They are distinguished from the latter species by the medially depressed groove and by the smooth MS (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFE9FFF3FB5B51D9FB012894" box="[1167,1273,917,943]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[189,232,1752,1778]" captionTargetBox="[198,1398,371,1626]" captionTargetId="figure-15@25.[189,1399,361,1664]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 14. Neostasina paraiso sp. nov., A−D: holotype, ♂ (USNM), E−G: paratype, ♀ (USNM). A. Left palp, prolateral view. B. Left palp, ventral view. C. Left palp, retrolateral view. D. TBE, detail, ventral view. E. Epigyne, dorsal view. F. Vulva, ventral view. G. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ag = anterior groove; ar = anterior rim; C = conductor; CD = copulatory duct; dRTA = dorsal branch of RTA; E = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; LL = lateral lobe; MA = median apophysis; MS = median septum; pt = tegular protrusion; RpPt = cymbial retroproximal protrusion; SP = spermathecae; TBC = tegular projection at base of conductor; TBE = tegular projection at base of embolus; vRTA = ventral branch of RTA; VTA = ventral tibial apophysis. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607950" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607950/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="188">Fig. 14E</figureCitation>
) (strongly recurved groove and MS bearing a posterior medial protrusion in 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFE9FFF3FC0F51F6FB8528E8" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayon" authorityYear="2016" box="[987,1149,954,979]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="22" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jamaicana">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFE9FFF3FC0F51F6FB8528E8" box="[987,1149,954,979]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="188">N. jamaicana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
