</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFE7FFFDFF6953DDFC932AF5" blockId="24.[189,1398,366,463]" pageId="24" pageNumber="190">
COLOR. Coloration pattern as in male, slightly lighter, with opisthosoma with few scattered brown spots dorsally and no distinctive pattern ventrally (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFE7FFFDFD1853F8FCD82AF5" box="[716,800,436,462]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="23.[189,231,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[193,1392,274,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-15@23.[189,1399,261,1915]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="Fig. 12. Neostasina paraiso sp. nov., A−B: holotype, ♂ (USNM), C−D: paratype, ♀ (USNM). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Habitus, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607942" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607942/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="190">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
